to notice a violent attack.

00:03:32.542 --> 00:03:33.542
6) Sniff and Spend
Shops use certain scents to create an emotional

00:03:33.542 --> 00:03:34.542
connection with customers.
Researchers found that shoppers in the presence

00:03:34.542 --> 00:03:35.650
of an orange scent spent on average 20% more.

00:03:35.650 --> 00:03:37.203
5) Pinocchio Illusion
Our ability to sense the position of our body

00:03:37.203 --> 00:03:38.203
parts can be confused by stimulating muscles.
Touching your nose while stimulating arm muscles

00:03:38.203 --> 00:03:39.203
creates a false sensation that your nose is
growing.

00:03:39.203 --> 00:03:40.203
4) Eyes Change The Taste Of Food
The color of food affects how we taste it.

00:03:40.203 --> 00:03:41.203
Scientists tricked wine experts into thinking
white wine tasted like red wine, just by changing

00:03:41.203 --> 00:03:42.203
the liquid's color.

00:03:42.203 --> 00:03:43.203
3) Nonconscious Process
30 areas in our brain process vision. Mistakes

00:03:43.203 --> 00:03:44.203
occur when a pattern associated with danger
is recognised before we consciously process

00:03:44.203 --> 00:03:45.203
it. e.g. we can mistake a clump of hair for
a spider.

00:03:45.203 --> 00:03:46.203
